# LiVEiT® Trademark Usage

LiVEiT® is a registered trademark.

The LiVEiT® name, logos and visual identity identify official products, services and documentation developed under the LiVEiT® brand.

This document explains how the LiVEiT® trademark may be used in connection with the open source framework.

---

# Purpose

The purpose of the LiVEiT® trademark is to:

* Identify official LiVEiT® products.
* Protect the integrity of the LiVEiT® brand.
* Prevent public confusion.
* Maintain consistent recognition across all platforms.

The trademark exists independently of the software licence used for the framework.

---

# Open Source Software

The LiVEiT® Framework is made available as an open source project to encourage learning, collaboration and community contribution.

The open source licence applies to the software and documentation included within this repository.

It does **not** transfer ownership of the LiVEiT® trademark or associated branding.

---

# Ownership

The following remain the intellectual property of the LiVEiT® project:

* The LiVEiT® name.
* Official logos.
* Wordmarks.
* Brand identity.
* Official artwork.
* Brand documentation.

These assets may not be claimed as the property of another individual or organisation.

---

# Permitted Use

You may generally:

* Refer to the LiVEiT® Framework by its official name.
* Link to the official repository.
* Develop software using the framework.
* Contribute improvements through the open source process.
* Reference LiVEiT® in documentation when accurately describing compatibility or integration.

References should always be truthful and should not imply endorsement.

---

# Prohibited Use

You must not:

* Present your own product as the official LiVEiT® Framework.
* Modify the official logo and continue to present it as an official mark.
* Register confusingly similar names or logos.
* Use the LiVEiT® trademark in a way that implies endorsement or partnership without permission.
* Remove trademark notices from official branding.

These restrictions help preserve the integrity of the LiVEiT® brand.

---

# Community Projects

Community members are encouraged to build projects using the LiVEiT® Framework.

Where appropriate, projects should clearly distinguish between:

* Official LiVEiT® projects.
* Community developed projects.
* Third party integrations.

Clear attribution helps avoid confusion.

---

# Attribution

When referencing the framework, use the official trademark:

**LiVEiT®**

The registered trademark symbol should be used where practical, particularly within documentation, websites and marketing material.

Repeated use throughout a document does not normally require the symbol to appear every time.

---

# Reporting Misuse

If you become aware of misuse of the LiVEiT® trademark or official branding, please report it through the official project contact channels.

Protecting the trademark helps maintain consistency for the entire community.

---

# Changes

Trademark guidance may be updated as the LiVEiT® Framework evolves.

The latest version of this Branding Guide should always be considered the authoritative source for trademark usage.

